You think I want
our best man passed over?

16:57.542 --> 17:00.040
Well, then,
don't pass me over.

17:00.042 --> 17:04.112
This is not the time to be
thinking about work, Thomas.

17:04.114 --> 17:05.280
Take some time.

17:05.281 --> 17:07.214
Take as much time as you like.

17:07.215 --> 17:09.251
No, I don't want time!
I'm sorry.

17:09.252 --> 17:11.685
I don't want... I'm sorry.

17:11.688 --> 17:13.253
I want the promotion,
is the thing,

17:13.256 --> 17:14.723
and I deserve the promotion.

17:14.726 --> 17:16.694
Give me the promotion, June,
I won't tell anyone.

17:16.993 --> 17:17.993
Please.

17:19.029 --> 17:20.566
Give me the promotion.

17:24.134 --> 17:25.267
Sorry.

17:25.269 --> 17:26.967
- I'm sorry, sir.
- It's all right.

17:26.969 --> 17:28.473
- Sorry, sir.
- Maybe next time.

17:30.139 --> 17:31.909
What up, McG...

17:34.779 --> 17:35.781
Bannerman.

17:36.178 --> 17:37.244
Congratulations.

17:37.246 --> 17:38.614
I didn't even want it.

17:38.616 --> 17:40.084
I was in Ibiza last night.

17:41.051 --> 17:42.317
Heavy lies the crown, yeah?

17:44.154 --> 17:45.252
Pow.

17:46.757 --> 17:49.025
I'm taking a break.
I'll be in my big office.

17:55.197 --> 17:57.232
<i>♪ I'm a rebel just for
kicks, now</i>

17:57.234 --> 17:59.067
<i>♪ I been feeling it
since 1966, now</i>

17:59.069 --> 18:01.572
<i>♪ Might be over now,
but I feel it still ♪</i>

18:02.138 --> 18:03.171
Come here!

18:03.173 --> 18:05.173
I gave my life to you!

18:05.175 --> 18:07.142
I gave you everything!

18:07.144 --> 18:08.780
Why did you treat me...

18:10.179 --> 18:11.312
I'm sorry.

18:14.318 --> 18:17.251
This might actually be
a blessing in disguise.

18:17.253 --> 18:19.821
Get some perspective.
Get a hobby.

18:19.823 --> 18:22.758
Get some dirt underneath
your fingernails.

18:22.760 --> 18:25.794
You sound like every employer,
teacher, family member,

18:25.796 --> 18:28.229
friend, and vague acquaintance
I've ever had.

18:28.231 --> 18:30.800
I'm going to take
your name tag now, Thomas.

18:30.802 --> 18:31.803
No, not...

18:33.337 --> 18:34.770
Welcome to Harrods.

18:34.772 --> 18:37.706
I hope you enjoy drinking
dirty toilet water.

18:37.708 --> 18:40.842
Might I suggest some time
in the country?

18:40.844 --> 18:42.042
It's calming.

18:42.044 --> 18:43.243
Serene!

18:43.245 --> 18:44.346
Hee-haw!

18:44.348 --> 18:46.313
Yeah!

18:46.315 --> 18:48.650
One hundred and eighty!

18:48.652 --> 18:50.822
Joust! Joust!
Joust! Joust!

18:51.021 --> 18:52.056
Ooh.

18:52.955 --> 18:53.957
Yeah!

18:55.058 --> 18:57.696
Streaker!

18:58.729 --> 19:01.963
Oh, yeah, now it's a party.

19:01.965 --> 19:04.570
- Hors d'oeuvres?
- I'll just take one.

19:08.237 --> 19:10.740
No, it's hitch kick,
then boogaloo.

19:10.742 --> 19:13.375
When am I going to
get to choreograph?

19:13.377 --> 19:15.076
When you're the oldest.

19:15.078 --> 19:16.745
Aw, I can't wait that long.

19:16.747 --> 19:18.747
Hey, let's go
get Mum and Dad.

19:18.749 --> 19:20.181
Where do you want it, Peter?

19:20.183 --> 19:21.348
Oh, anywhere's fine.

19:21.350 --> 19:24.251
I mean, maybe a...
Maybe a little higher?

19:24.253 --> 19:26.221
A lit... No, too much.
A little lower.

19:26.223 --> 19:28.694
Hmm, to the left.
No, to the right.

19:29.158 --> 19:31.358
More. Too far. Lower.

19:31.360 --> 19:32.993
To the right. Up.

19:32.995 --> 19:34.229
Lower. Down.

19:34.231 --> 19:35.396
Right. Right.

19:35.398 --> 19:38.032
Lower. Lower. Lower.

19:38.034 --> 19:39.702
Up. Middle. Left.

19:39.704 --> 19:41.435
Right. Lower. Up.

19:41.437 --> 19:43.338
Your right. My left.

19:43.340 --> 19:45.139
Your down. My up.

19:45.141 --> 19:46.407
Left. Right.

19:46.409 --> 19:47.745
Perfect.

19:48.812 --> 19:50.147
He's gone now, guys.

19:51.683 --> 19:53.619
I just wish
you were here to enjoy it.

19:55.351 --> 19:57.788
I'm never letting anyone
take it from us again.

20:13.771 --> 20:15.036
Thomas McGregor?

20:15.038 --> 20:16.705
Sign here, please.

20:16.707 --> 20:19.007
Oh, from Windermere?
Fancy place, that.

20:19.009 --> 20:20.710
I don't know anyone from
Windermere.

20:20.712 --> 20:22.010
Well, it's from
Unclaimed Property.

20:22.012 --> 20:24.011
Usually means
you've inherited something.

20:24.013 --> 20:26.414
<i>Inherited
something, he did.</i>

20:26.416 --> 20:28.818
<i>From that great-uncle
he knew nothing about.</i>

20:28.820 --> 20:31.319
<i>Turns out intimacy issues
run in the family.</i>

20:31.321 --> 20:33.789
Windermere?
That's in the country.

20:33.791 --> 20:34.724
Well, fancy country.

20:34.726 --> 20:36.895
The houses there
go for a king's ransom.

20:37.861 --> 20:40.127
Ransom enough to
buy my own toy shop?

20:40.129 --> 20:41.062
I'd imagine so.

20:41.064 --> 20:42.230
And fill it with the finest
merchandise?

20:42.232 --> 20:43.197
Should do, yeah.

20:43.199 --> 20:44.733
Ransom enough to have
tempered glass shelving

20:44.735 --> 20:45.769
and seasonal
window decorations?

20:45.771 --> 20:48.368
That I might have to do
some research on, sir.

20:48.370 --> 20:50.174
Can I get back to you
mail-time tomorrow?

20:57.313 --> 20:59.313
Round trip to Windermere,
please.

20:59.315 --> 21:00.415
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

21:00.417 --> 21:03.952
<i>♪ I don't give a damn
what the people say</i>

21:03.954 --> 21:06.221
<i>♪ I'm gonna do it my way,
gonna do it my way</i>

21:06.223 --> 21:08.088
<i>♪ Boom, boom, boom, boom,
and bang, bang, bang</i>

21:08.090 --> 21:10.125
<i>♪ I'm gonna let it all out,
do my thing</i>

21:10.127 --> 21:12.528
<i>♪ Boom, boom, boom,
and a bang, bang, bang ♪</i>

21:12.530 --> 21:14.361
Good evening. Are you
aware of this location?

21:14.363 --> 21:15.865
- The McGregor manor?
- Yes.

21:15.867 --> 21:17.232
- Is that where you're staying?
- It's just temporary.

21:17.234 --> 21:18.833
I am merely appraising
the manor's condition

21:18.835 --> 21:20.502
before putting it
on the market to sell.

21:20.504 --> 21:22.841
But you do want me
to take you there?

21:23.072 --> 21:23.972
Yes.

21:23.974 --> 21:25.007
- Well, hop in.
- Thank you.

21:25.009 --> 21:26.876
I think you're really going
to love living there.

21:26.878 --> 21:28.376
Please don't talk to me
on the drive.

21:29.411 --> 21:31.146
- Give it to me.
- Here.

21:34.984 --> 21:37.855
I can fly! Oh!

21:39.321 --> 21:40.822
I think I cracked a rib.

21:40.824 --> 21:42.190
How many ribs do we have?

21:42.192 --> 21:44.058
- Thirteen.
- No way.

21:44.060 --> 21:45.193
Sweet.

21:45.195 --> 21:46.529
Oh, no, but don't...

21:46.531 --> 21:48.032
I can fly...

21:49.232 --> 21:50.666
Oh.

21:50.668 --> 21:53.001
It's nothing against the country.
I just find it disgusting.

21:53.003 --> 21:55.270
Yes, you've made that
quite clear on the journey, sir.

21:55.272 --> 21:57.137
I would just like
the record to reflect that.

21:57.139 --> 22:00.140
Well, I shall create a record
and make sure that it reflects it.

22:00.142 --> 22:02.443
A human.

22:02.445 --> 22:05.146
Oh, dear. Everybody out! Out!

22:05.148 --> 22:08.818
Get out! Humans are coming!
Human! Human!

22:08.820 --> 22:11.386
You know, it's like, who am I?

22:11.388 --> 22:13.489
Who are you? Yeah?

22:13.491 --> 22:16.457
You know, like,
we're all connected,

22:16.459 --> 22:17.961
but with what rope?

22:20.030 --> 22:22.396
A human! Humans are coming!

22:22.398 --> 22:23.935
- What should we do?
- What?

22:24.901 --> 22:26.467
Everybody hide!

22:31.340 --> 22:33.974
Oh, your quills
are stabbing me.

22:33.976 --> 22:35.856
I wasn't designed for hiding.

22:45.155 --> 22:47.324
Who lives like this?

22:49.325 --> 22:51.091
Hit the lights!

22:51.093 --> 22:52.797
Oh, no. Tommy!

22:53.163 --> 22:54.864
Tommy, hide!

22:58.502 --> 23:01.135
No, just because
you can't see him,

23:01.137 --> 23:03.504
doesn't mean he can't
see you. Understand?

23:03.506 --> 23:05.811
- Mmm-hmm.
- Now hide!

23:06.309 --> 23:07.175
What? No, Tommy.

23:07.177 --> 23:10.310
Now you're just
posing as a candelabra.

23:10.312 --> 23:12.246
Now you're just a tablecloth.

23:12.248 --> 23:13.514
Now you're just a...

23:13.516 --> 23:15.183
What are you?

23:15.185 --> 23:17.151
I'm a lazy Susan.

23:17.153 --> 23:18.155
What?

23:21.190 --> 23:22.425
Tommy! Tommy!

24:00.697 --> 24:02.265
Get... Get out!

24:05.535 --> 24:06.904
Get...

24:08.437 --> 24:09.971
Get out!

24:09.973 --> 24:14.177
Every single one of you!
Out, you vermin!

24:18.716 --> 24:20.648
Stay out of my house!

24:20.650 --> 24:22.349
He had the key.

24:22.351 --> 24:24.520
He must be a McGregor.

24:24.522 --> 24:25.990
Oh.

24:27.491 --> 24:29.290
Headlights.

24:29.292 --> 24:32.292
Felix, blink.
Blink, blink, blink, blink.

24:32.294 --> 24:33.729
Come on, big guy.
Blink, blink, blink.

24:33.731 --> 24:36.030
Headlights.

24:36.032 --> 24:37.472
Come on, deer.

24:45.308 --> 24:47.075
The sun came up again?

24:47.077 --> 24:48.342
I can't believe it!

24:48.344 --> 24:50.979
I thought when I closed
my eyes last night,

24:50.981 --> 24:52.013
that that was it!

24:52.015 --> 24:56.384
But we have another day of this!
Whoo-hoo!

25:06.161 --> 25:07.464
It wasn't a nightmare.

25:11.001 --> 25:12.537
Oh. It's a nightmare.

25:37.561 --> 25:39.494
What is that music?

25:39.496 --> 25:40.530
I don't know.

25:40.532 --> 25:44.065
But it sounds very dramatic
and life-changing.

25:55.244 --> 25:56.512
Oh.

25:56.514 --> 25:58.614
Hello, sweeties.

25:58.616 --> 26:00.682
You checking
on the new neighbor?

26:00.684 --> 26:02.416
Don't worry.
He can't be any worse

26:02.418 --> 26:04.988
than the old crab bucket,
rest his soul.

26:06.055 --> 26:08.523
Never know, maybe he'll be
a nice, normal man.

26:08.525 --> 26:09.526
He looks nice.

26:10.126 --> 26:11.392
Looks very normal.

26:12.796 --> 26:14.598
That's not very normal, is it?

26:15.666 --> 26:16.764
That's normal.

26:18.502 --> 26:19.537
Hmm.

26:20.603 --> 26:22.369
Anyway,
it's gonna be exciting.

26:22.371 --> 26:24.371
We'll have somebody
new around here.

26:24.373 --> 26:26.574
They're not all bad,
I promise.

26:26.576 --> 26:27.810
I'll explain it to him.

26:27.812 --> 26:30.147
We all share
our land around here.

26:33.248 --> 26:35.151
I'm gonna give him the benefit
of the doubt.

26:38.688 --> 26:39.788
Oh, no.

26:39.790 --> 26:42.359
It's not over. We can
always go in the back...

26:43.460 --> 26:44.525
Or through the...

26:44.527 --> 26:45.529
Or use the...

26:45.862 --> 26:47.360
Or behind the...

26:47.362 --> 26:48.830
I didn't even know
that was a way in.

26:48.832 --> 26:51.466
I see the gates
are back up, huh?

26:51.468 --> 26:54.367
I guess you weren't
the prodigal son after all.

26:54.369 --> 26:56.839
That'll do, pig. That'll do.

26:56.841 --> 26:58.172
It was a fun night, though.

26:58.174 --> 27:00.676
I haven't eaten that much
in a long time.

27:00.678 --> 27:02.711
The diet starts now.

27:04.313 --> 27:05.314
Now.

27:06.315 --> 27:08.052
- Now.
- Hey, look.

27:09.252 --> 27:10.421
Now.

27:11.186 --> 27:12.521
Hello. Oh, sorry.

27:12.523 --> 27:15.756
I didn't mean to startle you. I'm Bea.
I just live over here.

27:15.758 --> 27:18.126
Oh. Hello. I'm Thomas.

27:18.128 --> 27:21.330
I live way over there
in London.

27:22.331 --> 27:23.332
That way.

27:24.300 --> 27:26.467
Yes. I'm just
here temporarily.

27:26.469 --> 27:28.301
I'm fixing up
this place to sell,

27:28.303 --> 27:30.171
using the proceeds
to open my own toy store,

27:30.173 --> 27:31.039
preferably near Harrods

27:31.041 --> 27:33.541
so they can witness
their own downfall.

27:33.543 --> 27:36.243
Oh, my. That's a lot
of information right there.

27:36.245 --> 27:37.310
- Sorry.
- Good for you

27:37.312 --> 27:38.279
for not being
afraid to open up.

27:38.281 --> 27:40.682
- What are they saying?
- Shh, I can read lips.

27:40.684 --> 27:42.415
I'm just a little
out of my element.

27:42.417 --> 27:44.653
I think you'll find the elements
here are pretty fabulous.

27:44.655 --> 27:47.622
"I think you'll find
the elephants around here

27:47.624 --> 27:49.560
"are really flatulent."

27:49.860 --> 27:51.091
What?

27:51.093 --> 27:54.361
In my opinion, it's just the
most beautiful place on Earth.

27:54.363 --> 27:56.633
Well, it just got
a lot more beautiful.

27:57.534 --> 27:59.102
Oh, gee.

27:59.637 --> 28:01.368
You didn't just say that.

28:01.370 --> 28:04.108
And clean, sturdy, functional.

28:04.542 --> 28:06.374
Oh, the gate.

28:06.376 --> 28:08.877
- Yes.
- I thought you were saying

28:08.879 --> 28:10.411
- I was beautiful.
- Did you...

28:10.413 --> 28:12.714
No, no, no. No,
I wouldn't say that.

28:12.716 --> 28:13.849
I wouldn't say that.

28:13.851 --> 28:16.349
- I would say that. I'm not...
- No, hey, I'm not fishing.

28:16.351 --> 28:17.819
- It's fine.
- You are beautiful.

28:17.821 --> 28:19.388
And you're different
to the gate.

28:20.925 --> 28:23.524
I can't read lips,
but I know her,

28:23.526 --> 28:25.694
and she's telling him
to take down those gates,

28:25.696 --> 28:26.928
and let us into the garden.

28:26.930 --> 28:29.230
Well, enjoy your brief stay.

28:29.232 --> 28:31.934
Just, please, don't be
like the nasty old man

28:31.936 --> 28:33.868
who used to live here.
He was a real twit.

28:33.870 --> 28:35.736
- He was my uncle.
- You didn't let me finish.

28:35.738 --> 28:37.140
He was a real...

28:39.677 --> 28:41.643
Sorry, I can't...

28:41.645 --> 28:44.780
No. There's no saving that one.
He was a real twit.

28:44.782 --> 28:45.848
- No offense.
- None taken.

28:45.850 --> 28:48.553
- I never knew him.
- You seem much more reasonable.

28:48.785 --> 28:49.918
Do I?

28:49.920 --> 28:52.920
Although, I must say, these
gates are incredibly sturdy.

28:52.922 --> 28:54.989
Are you expecting
an alien invasion?

28:54.991 --> 28:58.259
I just need to keep the
wildlife out where they belong.

28:58.261 --> 29:00.494
Well, they actually belong
everywhere.

29:00.496 --> 29:02.763
It was kind of their place
first. We're the latecomers.

29:02.765 --> 29:03.732
How long does it take to say,

29:03.734 --> 29:06.434
"Leave the gate open,
and let in the rabbits"?

29:06.436 --> 29:09.302
Leave the gate
open, and let in the rabbits.

29:09.304 --> 29:10.404
Ah, I certainly will, madam.

29:10.406 --> 29:12.840
And might I say, those rabbits
are incredibly cute.

29:12.842 --> 29:15.711
Especially the one
with the blue coat. He's my favorite.

29:15.713 --> 29:16.978
And, oh, here's a present.

29:16.980 --> 29:19.449
Wait. Why is she
bringing him a present?

29:19.816 --> 29:21.184
Oh.

29:21.517 --> 29:22.650
How nice of you.

29:22.652 --> 29:24.187
It's for bird-watching.

29:25.420 --> 29:26.422
Thank you.

29:28.492 --> 29:30.524
There's one. It has wings.

29:30.526 --> 29:32.527
Yes, that's a pretty
defining feature

29:32.529 --> 29:34.395
of the bird,
I think you'll find.

29:34.397 --> 29:37.330
You spotted your first bird.
Make sure to mark it down later.

29:37.332 --> 29:38.699
- Mark it down?
- Mmm.

29:38.701 --> 29:42.305
So there's a way of organizing and
documenting the chaos of the sky?

29:42.473 --> 29:43.370
Yes.

29:43.372 --> 29:45.610
Well, it was nice
to meet you, Thomas.

29:45.975 --> 29:47.343
Yes, you, too.

29:48.646 --> 29:51.378
And let's keep this
gate open, shall we,

29:51.380 --> 29:53.446
so the wildlife can run free?

29:53.448 --> 29:55.316
- Absolutely.
- She did it.

29:55.318 --> 29:56.687
We're in. Come on.

30:01.291 --> 30:03.359
Maybe it's not so bad here,
after all.

30:04.794 --> 30:05.796
Ugh.

30:11.768 --> 30:13.367
- No.
- I don't care.

30:13.369 --> 30:15.336
- I'm going in.
- Right behind you.

30:15.338 --> 30:16.570
No. Not a chance.

30:16.572 --> 30:18.473
You remember what happened
to Dad, right?

30:18.475 --> 30:19.808
But you go in all the time.

30:19.810 --> 30:21.075
That's my character flaw.

30:21.077 --> 30:22.677
You get your
own character flaw.

30:22.679 --> 30:24.945
- Come on, Benjamin.
- Why does he get to go?

30:24.947 --> 30:26.881
Yeah, why do I have to go in?

30:26.883 --> 30:28.483
Because that's
his character flaw.

30:28.485 --> 30:31.985
He goes along with everything I say, no
matter how stupid and reckless it is.

30:31.987 --> 30:34.422
No, I don't!
You're not the boss of me!

30:34.424 --> 30:35.724
- Benjamin.
- Coming!

30:35.726 --> 30:38.793
I can't let him go in by himself.
He's being stupid and reckless.

30:40.496 --> 30:42.329
I hope they're
going to be okay.

30:42.331 --> 30:44.465
They'll be fine, and if not,

30:44.467 --> 30:47.502
I guess I'll just be
the new head of the family.

30:47.504 --> 30:50.672
Peter, please be okay!

30:54.578 --> 30:56.677
I'm still
so out of shape.

30:56.679 --> 30:58.847
How's it working with the
putting the dressing on the side?

30:58.849 --> 31:02.587
Good. But I don't understand why it's
healthier to drink it all at once.

31:03.920 --> 31:05.288
Disgusting.

31:05.656 --> 31:06.658
Come on.

31:31.681 --> 31:35.383
What'd I tell ya?
Easy peasy lemon squeezy.

31:36.820 --> 31:38.355
- Rats.
- Run!

31:56.438 --> 31:57.908
Hello.

31:59.442 --> 32:01.879
This guy is so much faster
than the old one.

32:03.914 --> 32:04.949
Ah!

32:13.423 --> 32:15.155
Uh-oh. I think
we have a problem.

32:15.157 --> 32:17.626
- What is it?
- Everything's upside down.

32:17.628 --> 32:18.629
Where are you?

32:20.464 --> 32:21.995
We never should
have come in the garden.

32:21.997 --> 32:23.564
No guts, no glory.

32:23.566 --> 32:25.666
Are you ever
scared of anything?

32:25.668 --> 32:27.502
Yeah. Dying alone.

32:27.504 --> 32:29.570
That's why I brought you here.

32:29.572 --> 32:32.509
Do you know what we do
with rats in the city?

32:33.576 --> 32:37.647
We find them,
and we exterminate them.

32:38.948 --> 32:39.983
Ha!

32:41.651 --> 32:42.652
Benjamin.

32:48.524 --> 32:49.560
Ha!

33:01.871 --> 33:03.439
Ha!

33:05.073 --> 33:07.608
- Follow me.
- I can't see anything.

33:07.610 --> 33:10.144
- Follow my voice.
- I can't hear anything!

33:10.146 --> 33:11.212
Follow your heart?

33:11.214 --> 33:12.647
What?

33:13.583 --> 33:14.751
That way, that way, that way.

33:21.757 --> 33:22.759
Play dead.

33:34.003 --> 33:36.136
This is what happens

33:36.138 --> 33:38.973
when you make
a McGregor look foolish

33:38.975 --> 33:40.844
playing carnival games
in the shed.

33:42.978 --> 33:44.278
You see this, everyone?

33:44.280 --> 33:46.818
This is what happens!

33:47.551 --> 33:49.983
Why am I talking to wildlife?

33:49.985 --> 33:51.852
I am losing my mind.

33:51.854 --> 33:54.056
I do... They're not
going to respond.

34:00.996 --> 34:01.997
Come on, come on!

34:07.969 --> 34:08.971
Jump!

34:39.302 --> 34:41.301
Okay, okay.
Flopsy, take the bag,

34:41.303 --> 34:43.672
go to the window
and you put it over his head.

34:43.674 --> 34:44.675
Okay.

34:47.242 --> 34:48.810
Mopsy, you take the bag,

34:48.812 --> 34:50.976
go over to the window,
put it over his head.

34:50.978 --> 34:51.981
Got it.

34:52.179 --> 34:53.551
Oh.

34:54.181 --> 34:55.784
Cotton-Tail, take the bag...

34:57.654 --> 34:59.590
- Just give him a wet willy.
- Got it.

36:13.995 --> 36:14.997
No!

36:19.300 --> 36:20.367
You okay, big guy?

36:20.369 --> 36:22.002
Close one, huh?

36:22.004 --> 36:22.904
I could've been killed.

36:22.906 --> 36:25.710
And not just me.
What if he got the girls?

36:26.374 --> 36:27.944
This isn't a joke, Peter.

36:28.276 --> 36:29.647
I know.

36:30.146 --> 36:31.147
I'm sorry.

36:32.981 --> 36:34.815
You're all right though,
right?

36:34.817 --> 36:36.283
I got your jacket back.

36:36.285 --> 36:37.951
It's not as symbolic as mine.

36:37.953 --> 36:39.285
You know, not being
your dad's and all.

36:39.287 --> 36:42.022
And it's brown, too, which is a
mistake because you're brown.

36:42.024 --> 36:43.757
I mean, brown on brown,
who wears that?

36:43.759 --> 36:45.325
It's a bit matchy-matchy.

36:45.327 --> 36:48.127
Yeah, it's actually
a bit confusing.

36:48.129 --> 36:50.263
Half the time
we think you're naked.

36:50.265 --> 36:51.799
I just look for the buttons.

36:51.801 --> 36:54.167
But then one time,
it was your nipples.

36:54.169 --> 36:55.171
Huh?

36:57.940 --> 37:00.274
Anyway, you got it back,
and you're okay.

37:00.276 --> 37:02.911
No thanks to him. Look at him.

37:02.913 --> 37:05.178
Skinny bag of wet.

37:05.180 --> 37:07.884
Now, turn around
and drive us home, Eugene.

37:08.249 --> 37:09.951
Here's good.

37:09.953 --> 37:12.086
New to the area.
Probably take the next turn.

37:12.088 --> 37:14.120
Just using more fuel.
Not a surprise

37:14.122 --> 37:16.055
that he's not
environmentally friendly.

37:16.057 --> 37:17.926
Hey, we don't
inherit the Earth,

37:17.928 --> 37:20.728
we borrow it
from our children.

37:20.730 --> 37:23.330
I read that on a plastic cup.

37:23.332 --> 37:24.766
If you do a U-turn...

37:24.768 --> 37:26.900
It's actually a safe place
for a U-turn here.

37:26.902 --> 37:27.936
I think that's the...

37:27.938 --> 37:30.471
- Where...
- Where is he taking us?

37:30.473 --> 37:33.307
He's taking us into town.

37:33.309 --> 37:36.944
- So this is London.
- Wow.

37:36.946 --> 37:38.746
Big Ben! Wow!

37:38.748 --> 37:40.082
It's gigantic.

37:40.951 --> 37:42.884
I hope you appreciate this,
Flopsy.

37:42.886 --> 37:45.051
I never got to travel
when I was your age.

37:45.053 --> 37:48.857
What? You were my age,
like, three streets ago.

37:48.859 --> 37:50.225
It goes so fast.

37:55.064 --> 37:56.363
- Huh?
- Whoa.

37:56.365 --> 37:58.064
This must be Harrods.

37:58.066 --> 37:59.870
Wow. Classy.

38:01.471 --> 38:02.503
What can I do for you?

38:02.505 --> 38:04.203
I have a vermin problem.

38:04.205 --> 38:05.507
Rabbits, I'm guessing.

38:05.509 --> 38:07.441
- How do you know that?
- You're the new McGregor.

38:07.443 --> 38:09.343
- Bea's neighbor.
- How do you know that?

38:09.345 --> 38:10.980
- She mentioned you.
- She did?

38:11.514 --> 38:12.514
What did she say?

38:12.516 --> 38:14.281
That you want to sell
your house in a hurry

38:14.283 --> 38:16.884
and use the profits
to open your own toy store,

38:16.886 --> 38:18.151
preferably near Harrods,

38:18.153 --> 38:20.319
so they can witness
their own downfall.

38:20.321 --> 38:23.525
That's incredibly specifically
accurate, and a little disappointing.

38:23.527 --> 38:25.292
Who do you think
these guys are?

38:25.294 --> 38:26.561
They're wearing aprons,

38:26.563 --> 38:28.529
so that could mean
only one thing.

38:28.531 --> 38:29.997
- They're hedgehogs.
- They're hedgehogs.

38:29.999 --> 38:31.399
Hmm.

38:31.401 --> 38:33.332
Just make sure she doesn't find out
you're launching them rabbits.

38:33.334 --> 38:35.135
She loves 'em. Like family.

38:35.137 --> 38:36.938
Read their lips, Mopsy.

38:36.940 --> 38:38.138
If I was a learned fellow,

38:38.140 --> 38:40.439
I'd say she
anthropomorphizes 'em

38:40.441 --> 38:42.877
in lieu of any genuine
human interaction.

38:42.879 --> 38:44.211
But he's not a learned fellow.

38:44.213 --> 38:46.379
Which is why I think she's just
got a thing for those rabbits.

38:46.381 --> 38:49.415
"Which is why I think she's just
got a thing for most man butts."

38:49.417 --> 38:50.485
Huh?

38:50.487 --> 38:51.585
What would you suggest?

38:51.587 --> 38:53.255
An electric fence
will keep 'em out.

38:54.189 --> 38:55.191
To launch 'em,

38:55.957 --> 38:57.156
you'll need some firepower.

38:58.227 --> 39:00.359
Firepower seems like...
I don't want to...

39:00.361 --> 39:01.961
Get down.

39:01.963 --> 39:04.064
That's them! I knew it.

39:04.066 --> 39:06.165
Where are you?
I know you're in there.

39:06.167 --> 39:08.303
Come out! I saw you!

39:12.307 --> 39:14.106
Launch them.
I want to launch them.

39:14.108 --> 39:15.779
Right. Follow me.

39:21.050 --> 39:23.417
It's okay. I've got
11 more ribs.

39:23.419 --> 39:25.318
You actually have
13 on each side.

39:25.320 --> 39:26.287
What?

39:26.289 --> 39:27.922
Which is technically 26
because they go...

39:27.924 --> 39:29.523
Oh, now you're down to 19.

39:29.525 --> 39:31.191
Again, you push this button.

39:31.193 --> 39:34.026
The signal will travel
through the air to this.

39:34.028 --> 39:35.394
This'll start the spark,

39:35.396 --> 39:37.231
and anything
near it will explode.

39:37.233 --> 39:40.202
I do understand the fundamental
concepts of basic things.

39:49.010 --> 39:50.345
It's tricky. A little bit.

39:51.580 --> 39:52.949
Thank you.

39:55.484 --> 39:57.216
Thank you!

39:57.218 --> 39:58.285
Drive safe!

39:59.623 --> 40:00.755
Just match its speed.

40:00.757 --> 40:04.091
Our natural rabbits' pace
should be able to keep up.

40:10.667 --> 40:13.068
Do you know what?
That would never have worked.

40:19.974 --> 40:21.341
Watch it, boxhead!

40:21.343 --> 40:24.144
Leave him alone, babe.
He's just a country bumpkin.

40:24.146 --> 40:25.078
Morons.

40:25.080 --> 40:27.381
"Country bumpkin"?
I'm not a country bumpkin.

40:27.383 --> 40:29.982
I'm from London,
which is where I'd like to...

40:29.984 --> 40:31.421
- Thomas?
- Bea.

40:33.354 --> 40:34.924
- Hello.
- Hello.

40:35.659 --> 40:37.390
- How are you?
- I'm very well. You...

40:37.392 --> 40:38.225
What are you doing here?

40:38.227 --> 40:41.297
Oh, just...
Just picking up some, um,

40:42.330 --> 40:43.196
hardware.

40:43.198 --> 40:44.665
- It's lovely to see you.
- What?

40:44.667 --> 40:46.534
- Can I offer you a lift?
- Why is she here?

40:46.536 --> 40:48.636
Oh, no.
He's stealing her bike.

40:48.638 --> 40:51.370
That's all right. It's more
difficult than I thought it was.

40:51.372 --> 40:54.140
Oh, no. He's stealing her.

40:54.142 --> 40:55.376
Oh, no.

40:55.378 --> 40:58.278
She's going willingly and seems
to be enjoying his company.

40:58.280 --> 40:59.282
Come on, come on.

41:04.621 --> 41:05.989
Come on.

41:12.394 --> 41:15.028
That's a lot of smiling.

41:15.030 --> 41:16.430
More than before, even.

41:16.432 --> 41:18.031
She is showing more teeth.

41:18.033 --> 41:19.432
Must mean she likes him.

41:19.434 --> 41:20.701
Aw.

41:20.703 --> 41:22.169
Not "aw."

41:22.171 --> 41:24.706
She doesn't like him.
She's just really nice.

41:24.708 --> 41:27.207
She smiles at us all the time.

41:27.209 --> 41:28.378
Not like that.

41:37.554 --> 41:38.923
Come in.

41:41.323 --> 41:42.927
Would you like
something to drink?

41:43.325 --> 41:44.327
Yes, please.

41:45.327 --> 41:46.329
Oh.

41:47.162 --> 41:48.394
Are these your paintings?

41:48.396 --> 41:51.164
Oh, that's just
a work in progress.

41:51.166 --> 41:53.369
No, no, this is,
this is beautiful.

41:54.169 --> 41:55.234
Thank you.

41:55.236 --> 41:57.505
What a majestic
mountain range.

41:57.507 --> 41:59.106
It's an old woman in a hat.

41:59.108 --> 42:01.107
Right. Yeah. There's...
There's the hat.

42:01.109 --> 42:02.710
- That's her eyes.
- Yes.

42:02.712 --> 42:04.377
- And that's her chin.
- It's her foot.

42:04.379 --> 42:05.381
That's her foot.

42:06.716 --> 42:09.616
Oh. I'm allergic to
blackberries.

42:09.618 --> 42:11.786
- Oh.
- I'm sorry. My throat closes up.

42:11.788 --> 42:14.321
Allergic to blackberries?

42:14.323 --> 42:16.323
Is that even a thing?
Is that where we've got to?

42:16.325 --> 42:20.160
I mean, everyone's suddenly
allergic to everything.

42:20.162 --> 42:21.361
Stop using it as a crutch!

42:21.363 --> 42:24.430
You know, some people do have
legitimate medical conditions.

42:24.432 --> 42:25.766
Of course, of course.
It's a real struggle

42:25.768 --> 42:27.068
and my heart goes out to them.

42:27.070 --> 42:29.390
It's very tough, very sad. I
don't want to get any letters.

42:29.638 --> 42:31.773
But this guy, come on!

42:31.775 --> 42:33.406
Oh, what about these?

42:33.408 --> 42:35.242
That's just something
I do for fun,

42:35.244 --> 42:37.779
when I'm not focusing
on my real work.

42:37.781 --> 42:39.245
These are beautiful.

42:39.247 --> 42:40.480
You don't have to say that.

42:40.482 --> 42:42.583
I mean, they must be good
if I like them,

42:42.585 --> 42:44.184
given how much I hate rabbits.

42:44.186 --> 42:48.321
I mean, somehow, you managed to make
them look not like the vermin they are.

42:48.323 --> 42:50.625
Vermin? Vermin?

42:50.627 --> 42:52.527
- What does "vermin" mean?
- Like a rodent.

42:52.529 --> 42:55.663
Rodent? Rodent?

42:55.665 --> 42:56.797
What does "rodent" mean?

42:56.799 --> 42:59.131
Like a rat or a mouse.

42:59.133 --> 43:01.403
You think rabbits are vermin?
You're joking, right?

43:02.839 --> 43:05.104
Yes. I'm joking.

43:05.106 --> 43:08.307
'Cause I'm hilarious and
whimsical.

43:08.309 --> 43:11.410
Rabbits are actually
perfect creatures.

43:11.412 --> 43:13.080
They're generous,

43:13.082 --> 43:15.182
honest, pure.

43:15.184 --> 43:16.551
You should see the way
they talk to each other.

43:16.553 --> 43:19.086
They do this incredible thing
when they're apologizing.

43:19.088 --> 43:20.487
- Rabbits apologize?
- Mmm-hmm.

43:20.489 --> 43:23.158
They put their heads
together, like this.

43:24.292 --> 43:25.860
No. No, no, no,
don't apologize to him.

43:25.862 --> 43:27.694
Why is she apologizing to him?

43:27.696 --> 43:30.165
Why is she apologizing to him?

43:32.233 --> 43:34.869
Wow,
that's taking a long time.

43:34.871 --> 43:37.574
She's apologizing
the heck out of that guy.

43:39.207 --> 43:41.842
<i>And this was
only the beginning.</i>

43:41.844 --> 43:45.549
<i>It didn't get any easier for
Peter and the others to stomach.</i>

43:46.148 --> 43:47.451
<i>Or understand.</i>

43:47.717 --> 43:49.085
Anyway.

43:49.719 --> 43:50.851
You'll see.

43:50.853 --> 43:52.419
You'll grow to love them.

43:52.421 --> 43:55.421
<i>But romance
is a powerful thing.</i>

43:55.423 --> 43:57.724
<i>It can sneak up
on any two people.</i>

43:57.726 --> 44:00.227
<i>Even if one is amazing,</i>

44:00.229 --> 44:02.663
<i>and the other is a McGregor.</i>

44:02.665 --> 44:04.465
<i>♪ Girl, I say</i>

44:04.467 --> 44:09.305
<i>♪ If only life would
lean our way</i>

44:10.607 --> 44:14.341
<i>♪ Well, you and me
we'd run away</i>

44:14.343 --> 44:20.147
<i>♪ To be wherever
our adventure awaits</i>

44:21.316 --> 44:24.151
<i>♪ I heard your heart say
love, love, love</i>

44:25.621 --> 44:30.525
<i>♪ I heard your heart say
love, love, love</i>

44:30.527 --> 44:35.428
<i>♪ I heard your heart say
love, love, love</i>

44:35.430 --> 44:38.632
<i>♪ I heard your heart say
love, love, love</i>

44:38.634 --> 44:41.536
And after my parents
died, I was put in a group home.

44:41.538 --> 44:42.503
Peel.

44:42.505 --> 44:44.704
That must have been awfully
traumatic for you.

44:44.706 --> 44:46.238
Did you deal
with it okay? Peel.

44:46.240 --> 44:48.244
Didn't affect me in the
slightest. Peel.

44:48.844 --> 44:50.412
Yes, I can see that.

44:51.379 --> 44:53.245
Maybe I have some tendencies.

44:53.247 --> 44:55.949
Yeah, to commit rabbit-cide.

44:55.951 --> 44:57.451
- Is that a word?
- No.

44:57.453 --> 45:01.256
Well, I think we all have
our tendencies. Peel.

45:01.658 --> 45:02.790
What are yours?

45:02.792 --> 45:04.423
I guess I don't like people

45:04.425 --> 45:06.627
who aren't who
they say they are.

45:06.629 --> 45:08.194
It's more about me.

45:08.196 --> 45:09.296
I keep saying
I'm a real painter,

45:09.298 --> 45:11.964
yet I can't seem
to finish anything real.

45:11.966 --> 45:13.668
But she paints us.

45:13.670 --> 45:14.802
We're real.

45:14.804 --> 45:16.770
- Aren't we real?
- Ow!

45:16.772 --> 45:18.806
- Yep, definitely real.
- Huh?

45:18.808 --> 45:20.775
What do you miss
most about the store?

45:20.777 --> 45:23.511
And don't say, "Having
everything in its proper place."

45:23.513 --> 45:24.645
I get it.

45:24.647 --> 45:26.314
You have control issues.

45:27.216 --> 45:28.417
I miss being helpful.

45:29.350 --> 45:31.417
A parent or grandparent
comes into the shop

45:31.419 --> 45:34.386
looking for a gift
for the child they love.

45:34.388 --> 45:38.294
I ask a few simple questions, and
know exactly what they need.

45:40.462 --> 45:43.499
I love helping people
get what they want.

45:43.833 --> 45:44.931
You know?

45:44.933 --> 45:47.436
Especially when they don't
even know that they want it.

45:48.303 --> 45:49.438
Those are the best.

45:51.940 --> 45:54.674
Also, neatly arranged displays.
I'm sorry, I can't help it.

45:56.979 --> 45:59.714
Yes! Bananas! I win!

45:59.716 --> 46:01.648
Wait, "taradiddle"
isn't a word.

46:01.650 --> 46:03.984
Yes, it is. It means "fib,"
"pretentious nonsense."

46:03.986 --> 46:08.688
That is exactly the sort of definition
you'd make up for a made-up word.

46:08.690 --> 46:12.596
Mr. McGregor, are you accusing
me of taradiddling?

46:13.696 --> 46:18.598
<i>♪ I heard your heart say
love, love, love</i>

46:18.600 --> 46:23.336
<i>♪ I heard your heart say
love, love, love</i>

46:23.338 --> 46:25.037
Oh, no. Damn it.

46:25.039 --> 46:27.274
Come here, come here.

46:27.276 --> 46:28.478
I'll protect you.

46:30.012 --> 46:32.381
<i>♪ Love, love, love</i>

46:34.983 --> 46:37.352
<i>♪ Love, love, love</i>

46:39.755 --> 46:42.354
<i>♪ Love, love, love ♪</i>

46:42.356 --> 46:44.226
Come in. Come in, quick.

46:44.627 --> 46:45.762
- Huh?
- Huh.

46:50.600 --> 46:52.469
- Closed.
- Pull up a chair.

46:52.902 --> 46:54.735
We're wearing fur.

46:54.737 --> 46:56.737
- Thank you.
- You're drenched. Sit down.

46:56.739 --> 46:58.370
Let me help you dry off.

46:58.372 --> 46:59.509
Thank you very much.

47:15.090 --> 47:17.828
I could stay here forever.

47:19.462 --> 47:20.527
Hiya.

47:21.997 --> 47:23.630
Hello.

47:23.632 --> 47:25.964
Haven't seen you
in the longest time.

47:25.966 --> 47:27.935
Meet my new friend, Thomas.

47:27.937 --> 47:30.674
- Would you like to have a hold?
- Among other things.

47:33.008 --> 47:34.909
Oh, look.

47:34.911 --> 47:38.345
My two boys
getting along perfectly.

47:38.347 --> 47:40.815
Nothing could make me happier.

47:40.817 --> 47:42.482
Do you mind if I paint this?

47:42.484 --> 47:44.951
Nothing would make me happier.

47:51.093 --> 47:53.761
You're mine now, rabbit.

48:08.844 --> 48:12.880
Thomas, are your eyes emerald
or sea-foam green?

48:12.882 --> 48:15.414
Uh, sea-foam green with a hint
of battleship gray.

48:15.416 --> 48:16.585
I thought so.

48:23.859 --> 48:25.592
Thomas?

48:25.594 --> 48:28.961
And that's what separates us
from the French.

48:28.963 --> 48:30.864
Yup. Kiwi green.

48:30.866 --> 48:32.334
You're the professional.

48:35.571 --> 48:36.770
Yay.

48:36.772 --> 48:37.774
Ooh.

48:38.908 --> 48:39.909
Yay.

48:40.643 --> 48:41.645
Ooh.

48:41.944 --> 48:43.710
Yay. Ooh.

48:43.712 --> 48:44.944
Yay. Ooh.

48:44.946 --> 48:47.349
Yay. Ooh.

48:47.884 --> 48:48.949
Yay.

48:48.951 --> 48:52.585
No, no, no, it's an old woman
in a hat, you see?

48:52.587 --> 48:53.887
Huh.

48:53.889 --> 48:56.759
I just assumed she would've
reentered at that exact moment.

48:58.828 --> 48:59.830
Ow.

49:10.705 --> 49:12.071
You need to stop.

49:12.073 --> 49:13.643
It's not going to end well.

49:14.142 --> 49:15.645
I think I found it.

49:17.044 --> 49:18.414
The perfect ma...

49:19.046 --> 49:20.549
My painting!

49:28.055 --> 49:29.321
It's ruined.

49:29.323 --> 49:32.191
Oh, you know how uncontrollable
wildlife can be. I just...

49:32.193 --> 49:34.160
- Bad rabbit. Bad rabbit!
- Yes, bad rabbit.

49:34.162 --> 49:35.529
- Naughty.
- Bad rabbit!

49:35.531 --> 49:36.963
- Out, get out.
- Out.

49:36.965 --> 49:39.064
I said, shoo. Shoo!

49:39.066 --> 49:40.436
Get out of here!

49:41.202 --> 49:43.970
I'm so sorry.
He just went mad.

49:43.972 --> 49:44.974
Are you all right?

49:50.813 --> 49:51.948
He's gotta go.

49:53.013 --> 49:54.147
No way!

49:54.149 --> 49:56.216
The sun came up again!

49:56.218 --> 49:58.552
If I knew this was
gonna keep happening,

49:58.554 --> 50:00.721
certainly wouldn't have
fertilized all those eggs!

50:00.723 --> 50:03.590
Now I have to stick around
till they hatch!

50:03.592 --> 50:07.663
And be present and involved!

50:09.531 --> 50:10.764
<i>And so,</i>

50:10.766 --> 50:15.569
<i>Peter prepared his troops
for full-on battle.</i>

50:17.972 --> 50:21.574
Why you kids walking so slow?

50:21.576 --> 50:24.077
And that is how you
sneak up on someone.

50:24.079 --> 50:27.581
<i>♪ Come on, they're ten percent
